[Exodus 16:35](../../../bib/kjv/exo016.htm#035.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_035">exo 16:35</span></span>

manna

Manna, type of Christ as the "bread of life," come down from heaven to
die "for the life of the world." ([Joh
6:35](../../../bib/kjv/joh006.htm#035).md); ([Joh
6:48-51](../../../bib/kjv/joh006.htm#048).md). A "small" thing ([Exo
16:14](../../../bib/kjv/exo016.htm#014).md) having but the taste of "fresh
oil." ([Num 11:8](../../../bib/kjv/num011.htm#008).md) or "wafers with
honey" ([Exo 16:31](../../../bib/kjv/exo016.htm#031).md); it typifies
Christ in humiliation as presented in Matthew, Mark, and Luke; "having
no form nor comeliness; . . . no beauty that we should desire him" ([Isa
53:2](../../../bib/kjv/isa053.htm#002).md). But as such He must be received
by faith if we would be saved ([Joh
6:53-58](../../../bib/kjv/joh006.htm#053).md). To meditate upon Christ as
He went about among men, doing not His own will but the will of the
Father ([Joh 6:38-40](../../../bib/kjv/joh006.htm#038).md) is to feed on
the manna. This is, of necessity, the spiritual food of young believers,
and answers to "milk" ([Co1 3:1](../../../bib/kjv/co1003.htm#001).md);
([Co1 3:2](../../../bib/kjv/co1003.htm#002).md).

But Christ in glory, and the believer's present and eternal association
with Him there, answers to "the old corn of the land" ([Jos
5:11](../../../bib/kjv/jos005.htm#011).md) the "meat" of ([Heb
5:13](../../../bib/kjv/heb005.htm#013).md); ([Heb
5:14](../../../bib/kjv/heb005.htm#014).md) or Christ as presented in the
Epistles of Paul.

Compare ([Co2 5:16](../../../bib/kjv/co2005.htm#016).md).

